summary: An ordinance accepting deeds from William H. May and Anna May, George T. Dalton and Anna R. Dalton, his wife, L. B. Lovejoy and Winifred E. Lovejoy, his wife, Catherine A. Childs, a widow, Charles Albert Lawrence, Jr., a bachelor, Vivian Lawrence and John Lawrence, her husband, the Seattle Home Mortgage Corporation, George W. Brewer and Margaret Brewer, his wife, Fred C. Campbell, Absalom Gill and Theresa Gill, his wife, to the City of Seattle, for street purposes, and laying off 51st Avenue Southwest, 50th Avenue Southwest, and West Edmunds Street.
